    The Concept is a comprehensive functionality designed to enhance precision, synchronization, and control in CNC systems. It integrates multiple advanced features to optimize machine operations, ensuring accuracy and efficiency across various applications. Key functionalities include multi-channel control, enabling simultaneous management of multiple axes for complex machining tasks, and dual-axis synchronous control, which allows the main axis and secondary axis to operate at a predefined speed ratio while maintaining synchronization throughout the process. Perpendicularity compensation ensures geometric accuracy by correcting deviations in axis alignment. The Concept also incorporates rigid tapping functionality for precision machining, particularly in applications requiring high-speed, high-accuracy hole drilling. Polar coordinate interpolation enables machines to execute precise movements along circular paths, while parallel axis control enhances operational flexibility by enabling coordinated movement between axes. Real-Time Control Processing ensures dynamic responsiveness during machining, improving adaptability and efficiency. Additional features of the Concept include tool length compensation for precise machining, rapid traverse functionality for quick positioning, and minimization of data transfer issues. It also reduces operational expenses and enhances system reliability. The Concept supports LAN-based remote monitoring and Network DNC processing, allowing for efficient management of parts programs, PLC programs, and system parameters. Memory-type Screw Error Compensation further improves accuracy by correcting errors in screw mechanisms. The Concept's range extends from -9999 to +9999, providing ample capacity for diverse applications. It also includes an online adjustment feature for servo parameters and a lead error compensation function, ensuring optimal performance under varying conditions. Spindle speed control adds another layer of precision, enabling fine-tuned operations across different machining requirements. The Concept is associated with GSK direct drive technology, which leads industry change by offering advanced automation and control capabilities. It involves programmable logic controller (PLC) systems used in milling machines for automation and control, including functionalities such as arithmetic operations, conditional judgments, programming code definition, subprogram calls, user macro programs, system variable representation, axis-related alarm states, repeated action execution, and data parameters related to speed settings, deceleration control, stopping speeds, and minimum feed control speeds.
